<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="650">2.5. Retrieving order reports</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <strong>Process status</strong> tab contains information about order reports for your MFN orders. Use the <strong>Call schedule</strong> button to display the time interval in which Amazon generates order reports and the exact time of the next call.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="660">3. Activating the order referrer</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In order to link items, properties etc. with Amazon platforms, you have to activate the order referrer for those Amazon platforms in the <strong>Setup » Orders » Order referrer</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating the order referrer for Amazon:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Order referrer</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place a check mark next to the desired Amazon platforms.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="700">4. Setting the variation availability</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You need to activate all variations that you want to sell on Amazon country platforms. This is done in the <strong>Availability</strong> tab of a variation within the <strong>Item » Edit item » Open item » Tab: Variation ID</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Selling all variations of an item on Amazon country platforms</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you want to sell all variations of an item on Amazon country platforms, carry out the settings below for the item’s main variation. All other variations of the item then inherit the settings of the main variation.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating the variation availability for Amazon country plattforms:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item » Open item » Tab: Variation ID » Tab: Settings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the main variation in the <strong>Availability</strong> section.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Availability</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click in the selection field in the <strong>Markets</strong> section.<br>
→ A list with all available markets is displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select <strong>Web API</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus-square  "></i></span>).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the same list, select the Amazon country platform(s) on which the variation should be available.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus-square  "></i></span>).<br>
→ The market is added.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Multi-Channel</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings in the <strong>Amazon</strong> area. Pay attention to the explanations given in <a href="#item-availability-amazon">Table 5</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
