<h2 id="3150">17. Activating Amazon VCS in plentymarkets</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">First Activate Amazon VCS in the Seller Central</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Amazon VCS has to be activated and enabled in Amazon Seller Central first before you can activate the service in your plentymarkets system.<br>
When you activate Amazon VCS in the Seller Central, a date is displayed which indicates when Amazon will enable the service for you. Only activate VCS in plentymarkets on the date indicated by Amazon.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Do not use Amazon VCS and IDU at the same time</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you use Amazon VCS, you must not use <a href="#3175">Amazon IDU</a> because in this case, invoice documents would be uploaded to Amazon twice. This can result in missing invoices in the Seller Central due to throttling.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Amazon VCS is the VAT calculation service offered by Amazon. With this service, Amazon calculates the sales tax.  You decide whether Amazon invoices should be generated by Amazon or by plentymarkets. If you have plentymarkets create Amazon invoices, then the invoices are automatically transferred to Amazon.<br></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Activate Amazon VCS in plentymarkets in the <strong>Initial settings</strong> section of the <strong>Setup » Markets » Amazon » Select an Amazon account » Tab: Settings</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Invoices cannot be generated in other ways</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Note that Amazon invoices cannot be generated in other ways (e.g. manually or with an event procedure) once you activate the options <strong>VCS plentymarkets</strong> or <strong>VCS Amazon</strong>.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Best practice for Amazon VCS</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Also read the <a href="/en/markets/amazon/amazon-setup#markets/amazon/best-practices-amazon-vcs">best practice for Amazon VCS</a> which contains further information about the setup of Amazon’s invoice service VCS in plentymarkets.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating the invoice service Amazon VCS in plentymarkets:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Markets » Amazon » Select an Amazon account » Tab: Settings</strong>.<br>
→ <strong>Important:</strong> You first have to activate the invoice service in the Amazon Seller Central before carrying out the settings in plentymarkets.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select an option for the <strong>Generate invoice</strong> setting. Pay attention to the explanations given in <a href="#amazon-vcs">Table 15</a>.</p>
