<h2 id="3175">18. Uploading your own invoices to Amazon</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can upload the invoice documents that were created in plentymarkets to Amazon (Amazon Invoice Document Uploader - IDU) if you do not use Amazon VCS.  To upload your invoices to Amazon, create an event procedure in the <strong>Setup » Orders » Events</strong> menu.<br></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can upload invoices created by plentymarkets as well as invoices created with an external software to Amazon. However, invoices created by plentymarkets always take priority over external invoices. This means that all invoice documents will be checked and invoices created by plentymarkets will be uploaded first if available. If there is no plentymarkets invoice, the external invoice will be uploaded to Amazon.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Do not use Amazon IDU and VCS at the same time</div>
