<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="4100">21.4. Automatically transferring the shipping permission to FBA</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Set up an <a href="/en/automation/event-procedures">event procedure</a> to automatically inform Amazon about the order. After Amazon has received this information, the order is processed and the item(s) are made ready for shipping.</p>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title">Setting up an event procedure</div>
<div class="content">
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Events</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add event procedure</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus-square  "></i></span>).<br>
→ The <strong>Create new event procedure</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the <strong>event</strong> listed in <a href="#event-procedure-fba-shipping-clearance">Table 18</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The event is created.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out further settings as described in <a href="#event-procedure-fba-shipping-clearance">Table 18</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place a check mark next to the option <strong>Active</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The event procedure is saved.</p>
